---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "@/components/sections/PageHeader.astro";
import Container from "@/components/ui/Container.astro";
import { SITE_CONFIG } from "@/lib/constants";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Quickfire Firewood"
  description="Privacy Policy for Quickfire Firewood. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information in accordance with Australian Privacy Act 1988."
  keywords={["privacy policy", "Quickfire Firewood privacy", "personal information", "data protection"]}
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="How we collect, use, and protect your information"
    compact={true}
  />

  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-base-100">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <p class="text-base-content/60 mb-8">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> February 2026
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          Quickfire Firewood ("we", "us", or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy.
          This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your
          personal information in accordance with the Australian Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and
          the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>1.1 Personal Information</h3>
        <p>We may collect the following personal information when you interact with us:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact details</strong> - Name, phone number, email address</li>
          <li><strong>Delivery information</strong> - Physical address for delivery purposes</li>
          <li><strong>Payment information</strong> - Payment details for processing transactions</li>
          <li><strong>Order history</strong> - Records of your purchases and preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Communication records</strong> - Records of enquiries and correspondence</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 How We Collect Information</h3>
        <p>We collect personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Directly from you when you place an order, make an enquiry, or contact us</li>
          <li>When you complete a contact form on our website</li>
          <li>Through phone conversations when you call us</li>
          <li>Via email correspondence</li>
          <li>When you visit our yard for pickup orders</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.3 Website Information</h3>
        <p>When you visit our website, we may automatically collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your IP address</li>
          <li>Browser type and version</li>
          <li>Pages visited and time spent on our website</li>
          <li>Referring website addresses</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This information is collected through cookies and similar technologies to improve
          your browsing experience and our website functionality.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Process and fulfil your firewood orders</li>
          <li>Arrange delivery to your specified address</li>
          <li>Communicate with you about your orders and enquiries</li>
          <li>Provide customer service and support</li>
          <li>Send you information about our products and services (with your consent)</li>
          <li>Improve our products, services, and website</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
          <li>Maintain records for accounting and tax purposes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Disclosure of Information</h2>
        <p>We may disclose your personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our delivery contractors to fulfil your order</li>
          <li>Payment processors to process transactions</li>
          <li>Professional advisors including accountants and lawyers</li>
          <li>Government authorities when required by law</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties for
          marketing purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Misuse, interference, and loss</li>
          <li>Unauthorised access, modification, or disclosure</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Our security measures include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Secure storage of physical records</li>
          <li>Password protection and access controls for electronic records</li>
          <li>Secure payment processing through reputable providers</li>
          <li>Regular review of our data handling practices</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Access and Correction</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request access to the personal information we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction of any inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated information</li>
          <li>
            Request deletion of your personal information (subject to legal obligations to
            retain certain records)
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>To make a request, please contact us using the details below.</p>

        <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
        <p>Our website uses cookies to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Remember your preferences</li>
          <li>Understand how you use our website</li>
          <li>Improve website functionality</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings. Disabling cookies
          may affect your ability to use some website features.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for
          the privacy practices of these external sites. We encourage you to read the privacy
          policies of any third-party websites you visit.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on
          this page with an updated revision date. We encourage you to review this policy
          periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Complaints</h2>
        <p>
          If you believe we have breached the Australian Privacy Principles or have concerns
          about our handling of your personal information, please contact us. We will
          investigate your complaint and respond within a reasonable timeframe.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are not satisfied with our response, you may lodge a complaint with the
          Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC):
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Office of the Australian Information Commissioner</strong><br />
          Website:{" "}
          <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.oaic.gov.au</a><br />
          Phone: 1300 363 992
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For privacy-related enquiries or requests, please contact us:</p>
        <p>
          <strong>Quickfire Firewood</strong><br />
          Phone:{" "}
          <a href={SITE_CONFIG.phoneLink}>{SITE_CONFIG.phone}</a><br />
          Email:{" "}
          <a href={SITE_CONFIG.emailLink}>{SITE_CONFIG.email}</a>
        </p>

        <hr />

        <p class="text-sm text-base-content/60">
          This Privacy Policy applies to all services provided by Quickfire Firewood
          throughout Brisbane, Gold Coast, and surrounding areas of South East Queensland.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
